text: The Pakistani military has never been a united, disciplined, or monolithic institution. Its ranks seethe with ruthless ambition, extra-constitutional aspirations, and divisions. The first fissures surfaced as long ago as 1951, with the Rawalpindi Conspiracy, a coup planned by the then Pakistani Chief of Staff, Major General Akbar Khan.
